Notebook[{
Cell["ParallelTransport", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"12621411-e0aa-412c-82a8-277261420942"],

Cell["\<\
ParallelTransport[connection, proj, path] computes parallel transport along a \
path in the base space.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"300dedfe-987e-49db-a25d-a2e67b1ddbe0"],

Cell["Details", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"522863d1-1707-4404-858b-ee6a9d497380"],

Cell["\<\
path is a list of base vertices forming a walk in the base graph.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dbcd754d-5aeb-494f-8489-8660e493d261"],

Cell["\<\
ParallelTransport returns an Association mapping fiber vertices over the \
start to fiber vertices over the end.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ee277afd-d68e-4537-803e-a7d4e07f67d4"],

Cell["\<\
Transport uses FindHorizontalCurve to lift each fiber element along the base \
path.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fc899b72-51be-45f9-9f10-90581b28aab4"],

Cell["\<\
If a lift fails (no horizontal edge available), that fiber element is omitted \
from the result.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9674ad8e-b2f0-4d5d-aefa-f336fa077491"],

Cell["\<\
For a closed path (loop), transport gives the holonomy permutation of the \
fiber.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2ea699ea-d0b3-43a4-92ce-6c6643eadf00"],

Cell["Examples", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ac7bc3cd-9178-462a-94ef-bc58880b51c1"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`InfraGaugeTheory`\"]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"2a16569f-a7fa-445f-8f49-f6e36ee54bf6"],

Cell["Transport along a path in a cycle fibration:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6110f2b1-7535-45d7-b28d-9b0047f6a023"],

Cell["\<\
{total, proj} = RandomGraphFibration[CycleGraph[5], \"VerticalVertices\" -> 3];
conn = RandomConnection[total, proj];
base = ReconstructBaseGraph[total, proj];
path = First[FindPath[base, 1, 3, Infinity, 1]];
ParallelTransport[conn, proj, path]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"53b35406-c5b3-425a-86e5-70ded50306fb"],

Cell["Transport maps fiber over start to fiber over end:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"73bbd7fb-38b8-44ab-9063-61c4c687d7e3"],

Cell["\<\
{total, proj} = RandomGraphFibration[CycleGraph[5], \"VerticalVertices\" -> 3];
conn = RandomConnection[total, proj];
base = ReconstructBaseGraph[total, proj];
path = First[FindPath[base, 1, 4, Infinity, 1]];
transport = ParallelTransport[conn, proj, path];
{proj /@ Keys[transport] // DeleteDuplicates, proj /@ Values[transport] // \
DeleteDuplicates}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"67309b3c-104e-4265-a7f1-311ed9f0ee89"],

Cell["Trivial path returns empty association:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3bde8502-9b3d-4223-9d0e-670e9444ff93"],

Cell["ParallelTransport[Graph[{}], <||>, {1}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"026479ee-2bc6-44b2-be3d-da02814d52a8"]
},
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Mac OS X ARM (64-bit) (July 8, 2025)",
